    "introduction": "A recipe for Gl\u00fchwein/mulled wine a beverage you can find at almost every European christmas market. This recipe is my favorite one - optimized for flavor rather than alcohol content (it still kicks in). - \ud83c\udf7d\ufe0f Servings:1-4",
    "ingredients_source_text": "for 1 liter of Gl\u00fchwein - 300 ml Cassis-Juice (Johannesbeer), if you can't find it you can replace it with another juice, I did it e.g. with cranberry pomegranate juice - 1 bottle 700ml red wine (I prefer Primitivo/Zinfandel), don't buy a cheap cooking wine, you want to drink it :) - 50 g Sugar - 25 g Raisins - 1 orange - 1 cinamon bark - 1 spoon ginger powder (or a bit of fresh ginger) - 1 spoon cloves - 5 star anise - if you don't have the spices you can also just throw in sweet cinamon tea bags instead (or similar), they contain most spices - I took 6 teabags for 1 litre",
    "directions_source_text": "1. cut the orange in nice looking pieces (since they are mainly decoration) 2. throw everything in a pot 3. warm up (don't boil) 4. enjoy"
